This paper is about aerial image classification using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper proposes a novel end-to-end network that combines convolutional and bidirectional LSTM layers, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper also discusses the importance of capturing class dependencies, which is a topic relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
